Find the obvious errors in the following Java code for calculating an integer division between 2 local numbers.

```java
public class Main {
   private int a;
   private int b;
   private String unit;
   public Main(int a, int b, String unit) {
      a = a;
      b = b;
      unit = unit;
   }
   public void integerDivision() {
      int a = 42;
      int b = 21;
      String unit = "kg";
      System.out.println("b = " + b);
      System.out.println("a = " + a + unit);
      System.out.println(a + " " + unit + " divided by " + b + " is " + (a % b) + " " + unit);
   }
}
```

